如実
にょじつ【如実】 ﾛｰﾏ(nyojitsu)
如実に　truly; realistically; true [faithful] to life; as things really are; as one sees 《it》; 〔生き生きと〕 vividly; graphically.
▲如実に物語る　give a ⌐graphic [vivid, true] account 《of…》
・文字の乱れが彼の今の心境を如実に物語っている.　His confused handwriting bespeaks his present state of mind.
・練習をさぼるとそれが試合結果に如実に表れる.　Miss out on your training, and that will show up clearly in the match result.
・原爆ドームは原爆の恐ろしさを如実に表している.　The A-bomb dome clearly illustrates the terror of the atomic bomb.
・その作品は信長の特異な性格を如実に描いている.　The work portrays the special character of Nobunaga to the life.
・これらの写真では中東の惨状が如実にとらえられている.　The disastrous state of the Middle East is truthfully depicted in these photographs.
◧如実知見　awareness of reality; objectivity.
